1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:35,029 --> 00:01:38,341
(Nansha Dinner)

3
00:02:33,448 --> 00:02:34,608
Is she drunk?

4
00:02:35,448 --> 00:02:36,048
Not really.

5
00:02:36,608 --> 00:02:38,089
She really can hold her liquor.

6
00:02:38,888 --> 00:02:39,888
Is it done outside?

7
00:02:39,888 --> 00:02:40,969
When can I go back?

8
00:02:42,409 --> 00:02:43,608
You'd better not rush.

9
00:02:43,969 --> 00:02:45,289
I'll tell you when you can go.

10
00:02:46,048 --> 00:02:47,328
You really obey her.

11
00:02:48,608 --> 00:02:50,569
Ms. Zhao keeps you inside
for your own good.

12
00:02:51,529 --> 00:02:52,689
If you go without permission,

13
00:02:52,689 --> 00:02:54,129
you're responsible for any issues.

14
00:02:54,888 --> 00:02:56,809
Hao, are you into Ms. Zhao?

15
00:03:08,255 --> 00:03:12,520
=Episode 18=
(The Resolve to Fight Back)

16
00:03:25,928 --> 00:03:26,849
You scared me.

17
00:03:27,289 --> 00:03:28,448
Mom, you scared me.

18
00:03:28,448 --> 00:03:30,168
No, you scared me.

19
00:03:30,768 --> 00:03:31,809
What are you doing?

20
00:03:31,809 --> 00:03:33,128
Why haven't you gone to school?

21
00:03:33,488 --> 00:03:36,488
I'll go to school
after saying goodbye to you.

22
00:03:38,048 --> 00:03:38,768
You didn't know.

23
00:03:39,289 --> 00:03:41,928
Because you're asleep every day.

24
00:03:43,328 --> 00:03:44,249
Let me give you a kiss.

25
00:03:44,728 --> 00:03:45,208
Kiss Mommy.

26
00:03:45,849 --> 00:03:46,409
Go to school.

27
00:03:47,009 --> 00:03:47,529
Mom,

28
00:03:47,849 --> 00:03:50,089
go back to sleep after I leave.

29
00:03:50,608 --> 00:03:52,608
You woke up too early.

30
00:03:54,048 --> 00:03:55,328
Got it.

31
00:03:55,328 --> 00:03:56,409
Mommy loves you so much.

32
00:03:56,608 --> 00:03:57,728
Hurry up, go to school.

33
00:03:57,768 --> 00:03:58,608
Bye, Mom.

34
00:03:58,608 --> 00:03:59,689
Bye.

35
00:04:00,448 --> 00:04:01,289
You ate, right?

36
00:04:06,208 --> 00:04:08,369
Last Sunday, Ma from Binhu
celebrated his birthday.

37
00:04:08,369 --> 00:04:08,888
Thank you.

38
00:04:08,888 --> 00:04:10,009
Some old friends were there.

39
00:04:10,809 --> 00:04:11,648
Shen Mo went too.

40
00:04:12,768 --> 00:04:14,249
He brought another woman with him.

41
00:04:15,129 --> 00:04:17,729
Everyone could see what was going on.

42
00:04:18,888 --> 00:04:20,328
So they cut me off, right?

43
00:04:21,489 --> 00:04:22,609
Fine, let it be.

44
00:04:24,169 --> 00:04:26,848
This circle always fawns on the powerful
and neglects the fallen.

45
00:04:28,249 --> 00:04:30,088
By the way, I heard from Shen Mo

46
00:04:30,088 --> 00:04:35,968
they plan to set up a separate VIP club
with your company by year-end.

47
00:04:36,768 --> 00:04:39,929
They'll move all clients who meet
purchase targets with us into the club.

48
00:04:40,328 --> 00:04:43,609
What? What do you mean
by 'meet purchase targets with us'?

49
00:04:43,888 --> 00:04:44,929
How much is it?

50
00:04:45,328 --> 00:04:47,169
Five million a year
or ten million a year?

51
00:04:47,448 --> 00:04:48,169
I don't know.

52
00:04:50,129 --> 00:04:52,249
I just feel this news is bad for you.

53
00:04:53,609 --> 00:04:54,929
You handle major clients.

54
00:04:55,448 --> 00:04:58,448
If they move all your clients
to that club,

55
00:04:59,169 --> 00:04:59,968
you'd be...

56
00:05:03,528 --> 00:05:04,208
Thank you.

57
00:05:04,809 --> 00:05:06,369
This news is crucial for me.

58
00:05:06,369 --> 00:05:07,328
Thank you so much.

59
00:05:07,569 --> 00:05:08,328
Have you heard

60
00:05:08,328 --> 00:05:10,609
about the company
setting up some VIP club?

61
00:05:11,169 --> 00:05:13,569
To put all clients meeting
purchase targets with us together?

62
00:05:14,009 --> 00:05:14,648
No, I haven't.

63
00:05:19,689 --> 00:05:23,169
But I recall Xu Yuntian
mentioning it once before,

64
00:05:23,968 --> 00:05:25,489
saying Barry always wanted to do that.

65
00:05:26,009 --> 00:05:27,328
But Xu thought

66
00:05:27,328 --> 00:05:29,888
it was actually a way
to weaken his power.

67
00:05:29,888 --> 00:05:31,009
So he firmly refused.

68
00:05:31,288 --> 00:05:32,809
But Xu is gone now.

69
00:05:33,448 --> 00:05:34,288
Okay, I understand.

70
00:05:34,288 --> 00:05:35,129
Let's leave it be.

71
00:05:35,489 --> 00:05:36,489
Wait, wait.

72
00:05:36,489 --> 00:05:37,968
Don't be impulsive.

73
00:05:38,288 --> 00:05:39,609
I know you're anxious.

74
00:05:40,049 --> 00:05:42,609
But if this is something
Barry has always wanted.

75
00:05:43,169 --> 00:05:44,328
We can't change it.

76
00:05:44,328 --> 00:05:45,729
Even Xu was taken down by him.

77
00:05:45,729 --> 00:05:48,888
I can't just watch the company
take all my clients.

78
00:05:49,569 --> 00:05:52,169
Half my clients buy over five million
worth from me annually.

79
00:05:52,408 --> 00:05:54,049
If the company takes all my clients

80
00:05:54,049 --> 00:05:56,208
and actually sets up that VIP club,

81
00:05:56,528 --> 00:05:57,448
then I'm finished.

82
00:05:57,448 --> 00:05:58,848
It's like killing me.

83
00:05:58,848 --> 00:06:00,408
I know, I know.

84
00:06:00,648 --> 00:06:02,169
Let's figure it out together, okay?

85
00:06:04,249 --> 00:06:05,528
Do you have any plans tonight?

86
00:06:05,528 --> 00:06:06,208
Let's talk.

87
00:06:06,609 --> 00:06:08,208
I'm hosting dinner at Zizhuxuan tonight.

88
00:06:08,968 --> 00:06:09,729
Then tomorrow.

89
00:06:10,328 --> 00:06:11,809
Anyway, don't rush.

90
00:06:12,088 --> 00:06:13,848
This thing can't be solved quickly.

91
00:06:15,768 --> 00:06:17,528
I got it. Bye.

92
00:06:26,288 --> 00:06:27,768
I might overdrink tonight.

93
00:06:27,768 --> 00:06:29,049
Drink less and back me up.

94
00:06:29,408 --> 00:06:29,888
Okay.

95
00:06:30,768 --> 00:06:32,448
Just add these two dishes later.

96
00:06:32,448 --> 00:06:32,968
Come in.

97
00:06:32,968 --> 00:06:33,736
Should be enough.

98
00:06:34,968 --> 00:06:36,328
Mr. Du and Mr. Bi.

99
00:06:36,328 --> 00:06:38,088
Danning, you're looking more beautiful.

100
00:06:38,408 --> 00:06:39,408
I missed you so much.

101
00:06:39,408 --> 00:06:40,408
You look prettier.

102
00:06:40,408 --> 00:06:41,528
You guys look more handsome.

103
00:06:41,528 --> 00:06:42,129
Really?

104
00:06:43,208 --> 00:06:44,169
You're the big shot.

105
00:06:45,408 --> 00:06:48,049
Tell me, what should I do
about this situation I'm in now?

106
00:06:50,129 --> 00:06:51,768
I'm really struggling.

107
00:06:52,888 --> 00:06:53,648
I told my boss,

108
00:06:53,648 --> 00:06:55,088
"You want results?"

109
00:06:55,088 --> 00:06:56,888
"Fine, if you want results,
just tell me."

110
00:06:57,328 --> 00:07:00,169
"But stop messing with me
all the time, okay?"

111
00:07:00,169 --> 00:07:01,169
Yeah, that's right.

112
00:07:01,648 --> 00:07:03,208
I'm truly out of options.

113
00:07:03,208 --> 00:07:05,408
I think I should just switch careers.

114
00:07:06,169 --> 00:07:09,768
Mr. Zhang, you're in the cultural
and creative industry, right?

115
00:07:09,968 --> 00:07:11,528
I can do that too.

116
00:07:11,888 --> 00:07:13,489
I really like reading.

117
00:07:13,489 --> 00:07:14,968
Really, take me under your wing.

118
00:07:14,968 --> 00:07:17,729
I'm hardworking. I'm eager to learn.

119
00:07:17,729 --> 00:07:19,049
And I'm loyal too.

120
00:07:19,328 --> 00:07:20,088
Right.

121
00:07:20,088 --> 00:07:23,088
I'm sure your industry
needs someone like me.

122
00:07:23,088 --> 00:07:24,648
Danning, let's go rest over there.

123
00:07:24,648 --> 00:07:26,648
Seriously, think about it.

124
00:07:27,208 --> 00:07:28,088
Let's go over there.

125
00:07:29,448 --> 00:07:30,009
Take it easy.

126
00:07:30,729 --> 00:07:31,328
It's fine.

127
00:07:32,768 --> 00:07:34,408
Mr. Zhang, think it over carefully.

128
00:07:34,408 --> 00:07:35,009
Okay.

129
00:07:35,009 --> 00:07:36,288
I'm not talking drunk nonsense.

130
00:07:36,288 --> 00:07:38,009
Really, I want to change careers.

131
00:07:38,009 --> 00:07:39,448
I think your industry is good.

132
00:07:41,408 --> 00:07:43,129
Do you smoke, Mr. Zhang?

133
00:07:43,129 --> 00:07:44,408
No, I don't.

134
00:07:44,968 --> 00:07:45,968
Come on, have one.

135
00:07:45,968 --> 00:07:47,288
I quit smoking years ago.

136
00:07:47,288 --> 00:07:50,009
Then... then let's drink.

137
00:07:50,009 --> 00:07:51,169
- Alright.
- Come on.

138
00:07:51,169 --> 00:07:51,968
Let me do it.

139
00:07:51,968 --> 00:07:52,888
Let me toast you.

140
00:07:52,888 --> 00:07:53,729
Okay, alright.

141
00:07:53,729 --> 00:07:54,768
Cheers. No pressure.

142
00:07:54,768 --> 00:07:55,729
Okay.

143
00:07:59,208 --> 00:07:59,968
Take it easy.

144
00:08:00,169 --> 00:08:01,208
Alright.

145
00:08:05,848 --> 00:08:07,249
You'll always be my good bro.

146
00:08:07,768 --> 00:08:08,169
Okay.

147
00:08:08,528 --> 00:08:10,088
Seriously, keep me in mind.

148
00:08:10,088 --> 00:08:11,169
I can do it.

149
00:08:11,528 --> 00:08:12,768
I really can do it.

150
00:08:12,768 --> 00:08:14,528
Who says I can't?

151
00:08:14,968 --> 00:08:16,169
You can. You can.

152
00:08:16,408 --> 00:08:17,408
You can. No problem.

153
00:08:17,448 --> 00:08:18,129
Can I?

154
00:08:18,129 --> 00:08:18,489
You can.

155
00:08:31,648 --> 00:08:32,609
What are you doing?

156
00:08:32,609 --> 00:08:34,089
Why haven't I heard anything yet?

157
00:08:39,528 --> 00:08:40,609
How is it? Are you okay?

158
00:08:43,048 --> 00:08:43,648
Are you okay?

159
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:45,849
I just dodged, and then I...

160
00:08:46,288 --> 00:08:47,089
My leg.

161
00:08:47,408 --> 00:08:48,129
Be careful.

162
00:08:48,369 --> 00:08:49,369
Don't move yet.

163
00:08:49,489 --> 00:08:50,969
Squat down and see if it's swollen.

164
00:08:52,408 --> 00:08:53,729
Hold my dog for a sec. Thanks.

165
00:08:53,729 --> 00:08:55,568
It's fine. Check if it's swollen.

166
00:08:59,768 --> 00:09:00,329
Got it.

167
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:01,888
Thanks.

168
00:09:01,888 --> 00:09:02,609
Let me spray this.

169
00:09:11,129 --> 00:09:12,209
Once you get home,

170
00:09:12,209 --> 00:09:15,168
for the first 24 hours,
apply an ice pack.

171
00:09:15,168 --> 00:09:17,129
Then for the next 24 hours,
use a hot compress.

172
00:09:17,129 --> 00:09:18,168
It reduces swelling fast.

173
00:09:19,888 --> 00:09:20,969
You know a lot.

174
00:09:21,408 --> 00:09:22,849
I'm quite experienced with this.

175
00:09:24,849 --> 00:09:26,888
What's its name?

176
00:09:27,449 --> 00:09:29,648
Its... its name is Rich.

177
00:09:29,648 --> 00:09:30,329
Rich.

178
00:09:30,329 --> 00:09:31,168
Boy or girl?

179
00:09:31,168 --> 00:09:31,849
Girl.

180
00:09:32,168 --> 00:09:33,168
A girl, huh?

181
00:09:34,329 --> 00:09:35,408
You like dogs too?

182
00:09:36,768 --> 00:09:38,449
Rich. Why is it sneezing?

183
00:09:39,329 --> 00:09:40,009
Caught a cold?

184
00:09:40,288 --> 00:09:42,009
Its nose is usually a bit sensitive.

185
00:09:42,449 --> 00:09:43,729
Sorry, I need to take this call.

186
00:09:45,528 --> 00:09:46,969
Mei, Danning is drunk.

187
00:09:46,969 --> 00:09:48,129
You didn't come, huh?

188
00:09:48,729 --> 00:09:49,969
Come on.

189
00:09:50,729 --> 00:09:52,009
Everyone else came. Why not you?

190
00:09:52,456 --> 00:09:53,209
What scares you?

191
00:09:53,209 --> 00:09:54,609
Is Shen Mo your dad?

192
00:09:55,329 --> 00:09:55,969
Listen to me.

193
00:09:55,969 --> 00:09:57,009
I hold grudges.

194
00:09:57,009 --> 00:09:59,168
Don't give me
that 'family emergency' nonsense.

195
00:09:59,168 --> 00:09:59,849
Alright?

196
00:09:59,969 --> 00:10:02,888
I know you're just disrespecting me.

197
00:10:03,009 --> 00:10:03,849
Hear that?

198
00:10:04,568 --> 00:10:05,969
She won't let me take her home.

199
00:10:06,329 --> 00:10:07,329
She's calling everyone

200
00:10:07,329 --> 00:10:08,129
and cursing them.

201
00:10:08,449 --> 00:10:10,048
Hang in there for now.

202
00:10:10,048 --> 00:10:11,369
I'm coming right over, you hear?

203
00:10:11,369 --> 00:10:12,209
Okay.

204
00:10:12,209 --> 00:10:12,729
Bye.

205
00:10:12,729 --> 00:10:13,329
Bye.

206
00:10:20,209 --> 00:10:21,489
Can you walk home by yourself?

207
00:10:21,928 --> 00:10:22,768
No problem.

208
00:10:22,969 --> 00:10:24,249
I'll just grab a cab later.

209
00:10:24,249 --> 00:10:24,888
It isn't far.

210
00:10:25,129 --> 00:10:25,849
Okay.

211
00:10:25,849 --> 00:10:27,288
I have something to do. I'm off.

212
00:10:27,609 --> 00:10:28,369
Sure.

213
00:10:28,449 --> 00:10:29,089
Thanks.

214
00:10:29,089 --> 00:10:29,568
Bye.

215
00:10:29,568 --> 00:10:30,048
Bye.

216
00:10:30,048 --> 00:10:31,129
Rich, bye.

217
00:10:31,209 --> 00:10:32,048
Bye.

218
00:10:32,568 --> 00:10:33,168
Wait a sec.

219
00:10:33,576 --> 00:10:34,568
Can I get your WeChat?

220
00:10:34,568 --> 00:10:35,729
I need to pay you back.

221
00:10:35,729 --> 00:10:36,369
No need.

222
00:10:36,528 --> 00:10:37,288
I insist.

223
00:10:37,288 --> 00:10:38,288
Add me.

224
00:10:39,369 --> 00:10:40,209
I owe you one.

225
00:10:40,209 --> 00:10:40,849
Just add me.

226
00:10:44,849 --> 00:10:45,489
I'll scan you.

227
00:10:45,489 --> 00:10:46,129
Okay.

228
00:10:49,329 --> 00:10:50,376
Done, sent it over.

229
00:10:50,376 --> 00:10:51,009
I'm Lu Xiaobai.

230
00:10:51,408 --> 00:10:51,729
Okay.

231
00:10:51,729 --> 00:10:52,369
Thank you.

232
00:10:52,369 --> 00:10:53,168
Rich, bye.

233
00:11:01,129 --> 00:11:02,489
I got you a sports drink.

234
00:11:02,489 --> 00:11:03,089
Eases hangover.

235
00:11:04,408 --> 00:11:05,048
Thanks.

236
00:11:08,408 --> 00:11:09,209
I'll drive you home.

237
00:11:11,528 --> 00:11:12,288
I'm not going home.

238
00:11:13,408 --> 00:11:16,209
If my mom sees me like this,
she'll definitely chew me out.

239
00:11:16,849 --> 00:11:17,608
Then to my place.

240
00:11:19,888 --> 00:11:20,688
To your place?

241
00:11:21,129 --> 00:11:22,168
Li Dongming moved out.

242
00:11:30,888 --> 00:11:32,648
I want to find a place
to have some congee.

243
00:11:32,648 --> 00:11:33,969
My stomach feels awful.

244
00:11:36,369 --> 00:11:36,808
Coming.

245
00:11:37,369 --> 00:11:39,489
He's been a loyal client
for so many years.

246
00:11:40,329 --> 00:11:42,209
Hearing that Shen Mo and I broke up,

247
00:11:42,369 --> 00:11:43,768
he stopped placing orders with me.

248
00:11:45,129 --> 00:11:46,568
I wish I'd never dated Shen Mo.

249
00:11:46,888 --> 00:11:47,408
Really.

250
00:11:48,768 --> 00:11:50,369
I called Shen Mo, but he didn't answer.

251
00:11:52,888 --> 00:11:53,888
You called him?

252
00:11:54,129 --> 00:11:56,408
I need to clear things up with him.

253
00:11:57,168 --> 00:11:58,849
Relationships

254
00:11:58,849 --> 00:12:00,489
should end amicably.

255
00:12:00,609 --> 00:12:02,168
Why is he hurting my business?

256
00:12:02,609 --> 00:12:04,249
And that so-called VIP club.

257
00:12:04,489 --> 00:12:05,928
It's obviously targeting me.

258
00:12:06,329 --> 00:12:08,408
Is he acting out of spite
after a failed romance?

259
00:12:08,928 --> 00:12:11,288
Am I really that adorable?

260
00:12:13,609 --> 00:12:14,808
Stop smiling.

261
00:12:15,489 --> 00:12:16,888
I'm furious.

262
00:12:16,888 --> 00:12:18,888
Seriously, I'm furious.

263
00:12:19,249 --> 00:12:20,888
He got Jin to place orders with me.

264
00:12:21,768 --> 00:12:24,009
I could have just accepted them, right?

265
00:12:24,009 --> 00:12:26,648
Why did I have to make him
fall out with Jin?

266
00:12:27,369 --> 00:12:28,528
Who is Jin?

267
00:12:28,528 --> 00:12:30,449
Jin is the guy who brings him money.

268
00:12:30,449 --> 00:12:31,808
Who do I think I am?

269
00:12:35,928 --> 00:12:41,288
The biggest pitfall I've encountered
in my ten-year career. It's a cash vow.

270
00:12:43,209 --> 00:12:44,849
And I messed it up just like that.

271
00:12:46,768 --> 00:12:48,888
You messed it up
because you truly fell for him.

272
00:12:55,249 --> 00:12:55,808
Yeah.

273
00:12:56,249 --> 00:12:58,528
I admit, I really did fall for him.

274
00:13:02,369 --> 00:13:07,408
An old house on fire. It scared even me.

275
00:13:08,888 --> 00:13:09,969
I, Liang Danning,

276
00:13:10,688 --> 00:13:12,568
have been selling liquor
for over a decade.

277
00:13:12,568 --> 00:13:14,249
And I've seen all kinds of shady people.

278
00:13:14,249 --> 00:13:15,249
But in the end,

279
00:13:16,209 --> 00:13:19,209
I still plunged headfirst
into that silly love bubble.

280
00:13:26,408 --> 00:13:27,849
Shen Mo is quite handsome.

281
00:13:28,129 --> 00:13:29,489
Right? You think so too?

282
00:13:32,369 --> 00:13:33,768
Although he's a bit older,

283
00:13:36,489 --> 00:13:38,489
he's still very charming.

284
00:13:41,768 --> 00:13:42,408
You know?

285
00:13:42,408 --> 00:13:44,729
Back when we climbed Changbai Mountain,

286
00:13:46,249 --> 00:13:47,888
there was
a really steep section of steps.

287
00:13:48,729 --> 00:13:49,568
And

288
00:13:50,408 --> 00:13:51,849
he was walking ahead of me.

289
00:13:52,369 --> 00:13:55,568
He just turned around
naturally like this

290
00:13:57,288 --> 00:13:59,288
and supported me with his hand.

291
00:13:59,729 --> 00:14:01,449
Five words came to my mind.

292
00:14:02,768 --> 00:14:03,609
What five words?

293
00:14:04,648 --> 00:14:05,849
Oh my god,

294
00:14:05,888 --> 00:14:08,129
where did such a handsome older man
come from?

295
00:14:08,849 --> 00:14:10,528
That's way more than five words.

296
00:14:16,489 --> 00:14:17,449
What about you?

297
00:14:21,648 --> 00:14:22,648
I confronted him.

298
00:14:25,009 --> 00:14:26,009
Li Dongming agreed?

299
00:14:29,648 --> 00:14:30,849
He rambled a lot.

300
00:14:31,089 --> 00:14:33,089
Li Dongming does love you.

301
00:14:33,449 --> 00:14:35,568
Or he wouldn't have
told you about the shares.

302
00:14:38,249 --> 00:14:40,688
I bet now he really regrets telling me.

303
00:14:41,249 --> 00:14:42,648
Who wouldn't regret it?

304
00:14:42,729 --> 00:14:44,288
That's 15 million.

305
00:14:44,288 --> 00:14:45,888
Not just 1,500 yuan.

306
00:14:50,249 --> 00:14:51,609
Imported spirits with herbal tea?

307
00:14:51,969 --> 00:14:53,249
How retro.

308
00:14:54,849 --> 00:14:57,288
The old school defines classic.

309
00:14:57,408 --> 00:14:59,168
You know how they taste mixed together.

310
00:14:59,369 --> 00:14:59,888
Excellent.

311
00:15:00,888 --> 00:15:03,129
Your place should've stocked
some imported spirits.

312
00:15:03,369 --> 00:15:04,648
I had to go to the supermarket.

313
00:15:05,528 --> 00:15:07,489
When we sell imported spirits,

314
00:15:07,768 --> 00:15:09,608
we can only order
up to two bottles each time.

315
00:15:09,888 --> 00:15:12,089
We can't get good wholesale prices
or sell high.

316
00:15:12,729 --> 00:15:14,609
Better avoid extra trouble.

317
00:15:14,888 --> 00:15:16,048
Isn't business pretty good?

318
00:15:20,776 --> 00:15:23,720
(Lao You Eatery)

319
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:26,665
(Grand Stage)

320
00:15:26,665 --> 00:15:28,584
(Yellow Beef)

321
00:15:31,129 --> 00:15:34,249
You all usually just hunt
for cheap stuff online

322
00:15:34,489 --> 00:15:38,449
or buy a few bottles
from local wholesalers, right?

323
00:15:38,449 --> 00:15:39,449
That's right.

324
00:15:39,449 --> 00:15:40,329
Yeah.

325
00:15:40,768 --> 00:15:42,089
Hey buddy, stop pouring tea.

326
00:15:42,089 --> 00:15:42,969
Pour the liquor.

327
00:15:43,768 --> 00:15:44,449
Mr. Tan,

328
00:15:44,568 --> 00:15:46,688
don't drink too much
and miss profit tips.

329
00:15:46,808 --> 00:15:48,089
Pour him liquor. Come on.

330
00:15:48,089 --> 00:15:48,849
Underestimate me?

331
00:15:49,688 --> 00:15:51,408
But doing it that way has two issues.

332
00:15:51,969 --> 00:15:54,249
First, prices aren't favorable.

333
00:15:54,489 --> 00:15:56,888
Second, worrying about fakes, right?

334
00:15:56,888 --> 00:15:57,489
Yes.

335
00:15:57,489 --> 00:15:58,089
Yes.

336
00:15:58,209 --> 00:15:59,849
Counterfeit liquor is my biggest fear.

337
00:16:00,449 --> 00:16:02,849
Even if customers asked me
to sell it, I wouldn't.

338
00:16:03,168 --> 00:16:05,449
If you could get stock directly
from our company,

339
00:16:05,449 --> 00:16:06,329
would you do it?

340
00:16:06,449 --> 00:16:07,168
How?

341
00:16:08,209 --> 00:16:11,089
Ordering from their company
means multiple cases at once.

342
00:16:11,928 --> 00:16:13,688
And paying upfront in full.

343
00:16:14,048 --> 00:16:17,089
Should I hoard it at home
like vintage wine

344
00:16:17,688 --> 00:16:19,089
and sell it in 18 years?

345
00:16:21,209 --> 00:16:23,209
If I arrange consignment,

346
00:16:23,449 --> 00:16:24,688
you can take stock first

347
00:16:24,688 --> 00:16:26,808
and pay me after selling it.

348
00:16:27,168 --> 00:16:28,209
Would you be willing?

349
00:16:28,209 --> 00:16:28,928
Sure.

350
00:16:29,089 --> 00:16:29,969
But can you do it?

351
00:16:30,288 --> 00:16:32,288
That becomes my problem to solve.

352
00:16:32,688 --> 00:16:33,449
Can you do it?

353
00:16:33,449 --> 00:16:34,209
No problem.

354
00:16:34,209 --> 00:16:34,928
Can you do it?

355
00:16:34,928 --> 00:16:35,729
Can you do it?

356
00:16:36,048 --> 00:16:37,209
It's how we usually stock up.

357
00:16:37,209 --> 00:16:38,209
Then no problem.

358
00:16:38,209 --> 00:16:38,609
Let's try.

359
00:16:38,609 --> 00:16:39,568
No problem?

360
00:16:39,609 --> 00:16:40,408
Yes.

361
00:16:40,408 --> 00:16:41,168
Cheers!

362
00:16:41,609 --> 00:16:42,449
Come on.

363
00:16:42,928 --> 00:16:45,168
- To great partnership.
- To great partnership.

364
00:16:48,168 --> 00:16:49,688
I happen to have contracts with me.

365
00:16:50,089 --> 00:16:51,048
They're simple.

366
00:16:51,489 --> 00:16:52,969
You will understand at a glance.

367
00:16:53,449 --> 00:16:55,089
If everything looks okay to you,

368
00:16:55,089 --> 00:16:56,329
we can proceed.

369
00:16:57,089 --> 00:16:57,648
Take a look.

370
00:16:58,329 --> 00:16:59,209
Well,

371
00:16:59,729 --> 00:17:02,329
three to five bottles per shop

372
00:17:02,808 --> 00:17:05,128
means several cases for a dozen shops.

373
00:17:05,489 --> 00:17:06,449
If we really push it,

374
00:17:06,449 --> 00:17:08,409
it could equal
several regular clients a month.

375
00:17:10,088 --> 00:17:12,528
Get the warehouse to ship it ASAP
when you're back.

376
00:17:13,489 --> 00:17:14,009
Danning,

377
00:17:14,209 --> 00:17:16,088
our company requires cash payments.

378
00:17:16,768 --> 00:17:17,969
Can you nail consignment?

379
00:17:18,209 --> 00:17:19,608
Nail my foot.

380
00:17:19,608 --> 00:17:21,209
I'm fronting the money myself.

381
00:17:21,929 --> 00:17:22,969
So pay has to be daily.

382
00:17:22,969 --> 00:17:24,729
Otherwise, I can't keep cash flowing.

383
00:17:25,489 --> 00:17:26,169
But it's doable.

384
00:17:26,808 --> 00:17:28,048
Slower shipments are fine.

385
00:17:28,048 --> 00:17:29,288
Liquor doesn't expire anyway.

386
00:17:29,489 --> 00:17:31,169
But isn't this against protocol?

387
00:17:31,449 --> 00:17:32,288
Protocol?

388
00:17:32,808 --> 00:17:34,409
If sales had to follow protocol,

389
00:17:34,409 --> 00:17:35,768
you'd be starving.

390
00:17:37,969 --> 00:17:39,249
Don't sell me out, got it?

391
00:17:39,689 --> 00:17:40,969
I absolutely won't.

392
00:17:41,169 --> 00:17:43,689
I'm just worried it's too risky for you.

393
00:17:44,209 --> 00:17:45,689
If I didn't dare take this risk,

394
00:17:45,689 --> 00:17:46,889
I wouldn't be Liang Danning.

395
00:17:48,689 --> 00:17:49,528
Ms. Zhang.

396
00:17:51,048 --> 00:17:51,568
Slowly.

397
00:17:52,048 --> 00:17:52,368
Thanks.

398
00:17:52,368 --> 00:17:52,969
Ms. Liu, right?

399
00:17:57,969 --> 00:17:58,689
I'll head over.

400
00:17:58,689 --> 00:17:59,169
Your turn.

401
00:18:01,568 --> 00:18:02,088
What's wrong?

402
00:18:02,088 --> 00:18:03,328
Ms. Liu, please wait a moment.

403
00:18:09,088 --> 00:18:09,489
Boss,

404
00:18:10,568 --> 00:18:13,608
the champagne robing cart
worked incredibly well.

405
00:18:13,808 --> 00:18:15,088
The photos are viral online.

406
00:18:15,088 --> 00:18:16,264
The conversion rate is high.

407
00:18:16,449 --> 00:18:18,088
The target customers for Moonlight City

408
00:18:18,088 --> 00:18:20,288
are women
who enjoy champagne and nightlife.

409
00:18:20,929 --> 00:18:23,288
We can't exactly reach them
at nightclubs.

410
00:18:23,608 --> 00:18:25,288
So we intercept them after work.

411
00:18:25,649 --> 00:18:27,969
I'll send out the rollout plan
for the follow-up tonight.

412
00:18:29,969 --> 00:18:30,768
Speaking of that,

413
00:18:31,048 --> 00:18:32,409
supporting activities aren't good.

414
00:18:32,969 --> 00:18:34,489
We need a combination of strategies.

415
00:18:35,209 --> 00:18:37,048
We can't rely entirely
on the event company.

416
00:18:37,048 --> 00:18:39,848
Their grasp of the product and customers
is surely inferior to ours.

417
00:18:41,009 --> 00:18:45,009
Also, year-end holidays are near.
We must act quickly.

418
00:18:45,889 --> 00:18:48,048
For those ideas
that are labor-intensive and expensive,

419
00:18:48,048 --> 00:18:49,328
please keep them to yourselves.

420
00:18:49,689 --> 00:18:53,808
We could select shopping malls
with high foot traffic.

421
00:18:54,048 --> 00:18:55,489
Then we could mix cocktails on-site.

422
00:18:55,768 --> 00:18:58,649
We could make the colors
look really appealing,

423
00:18:58,649 --> 00:18:59,969
so people want to take photos

424
00:18:59,969 --> 00:19:00,808
as Moments posts.

425
00:19:00,808 --> 00:19:01,729
Cups must be beautiful

426
00:19:01,889 --> 00:19:02,969
with our logo on them,

427
00:19:02,969 --> 00:19:04,449
so when people see them,

428
00:19:04,608 --> 00:19:05,848
they'll want to keep them.

429
00:19:06,489 --> 00:19:08,608
This somewhat lowers
our brand's prestige.

430
00:19:09,088 --> 00:19:10,288
We sell whiskey, after all.

431
00:19:10,409 --> 00:19:11,169
Not bubble tea.

432
00:19:11,489 --> 00:19:13,328
And our main clients are distributors.

433
00:19:13,449 --> 00:19:14,768
Not those end-consumer walk-ins.

434
00:19:15,368 --> 00:19:18,889
But the influence of end-consumers
can pressure distributors to order.

435
00:19:19,169 --> 00:19:19,889
Quick point.

436
00:19:19,912 --> 00:19:21,288
Distributors only value rebates.

437
00:19:21,288 --> 00:19:22,048
Nothing else.

438
00:19:22,209 --> 00:19:23,288
They also like beauties.

439
00:19:23,449 --> 00:19:24,568
We could have more beauties.

440
00:19:25,088 --> 00:19:28,169
All our competitors
play the beauty card.

441
00:19:28,288 --> 00:19:29,209
What if

442
00:19:29,209 --> 00:19:30,848
the beauty card is just the best play?

443
00:19:31,088 --> 00:19:32,249
We have existing beauties.

444
00:19:32,489 --> 00:19:33,489
No extra cost needed.

445
00:19:33,768 --> 00:19:35,368
But isn't that too tacky?

446
00:19:35,528 --> 00:19:37,128
It is tacky, but it's effective.

447
00:19:37,489 --> 00:19:39,729
I think our company
isn't suited for the beauty card.

448
00:19:40,649 --> 00:19:42,128
Mr. Xu's incident just happened.

449
00:19:42,449 --> 00:19:43,808
We're under intense scrutiny.

450
00:19:43,808 --> 00:19:46,288
Isn't intense scrutiny
the best time for publicity?

451
00:19:46,768 --> 00:19:47,608
All right.

452
00:19:48,249 --> 00:19:49,729
I asked you to speed things up,

453
00:19:49,729 --> 00:19:51,689
not necessarily
to reach a conclusion now.

454
00:19:52,848 --> 00:19:54,536
Wang Hao's on-site cocktail idea
is good.

455
00:19:54,889 --> 00:19:56,768
Trendy and appealing
to the young generation.

456
00:19:57,048 --> 00:19:58,608
Send a complete proposal to me later.

457
00:19:59,088 --> 00:19:59,489
Okay.

458
00:19:59,808 --> 00:20:01,768
I still think the beauty factor
is more important.

459
00:20:02,209 --> 00:20:03,689
It's inherent to the industry.

460
00:20:03,689 --> 00:20:05,088
Why pretend we don't see it?

461
00:20:05,288 --> 00:20:06,169
Ding Wei, stop.

462
00:20:06,169 --> 00:20:07,288
I'm not wrong.

463
00:20:07,288 --> 00:20:08,729
Classics become classics

464
00:20:08,729 --> 00:20:09,889
for inherent reasons.

465
00:20:10,048 --> 00:20:12,489
Our main consumer group
is successful men.

466
00:20:12,489 --> 00:20:15,048
Not people walking down the street
sipping bubble tea.

467
00:20:15,048 --> 00:20:16,288
Ding Wei, could you stop?

468
00:20:16,368 --> 00:20:17,608
Why should I stop?

469
00:20:17,608 --> 00:20:18,848
Because you're her confidant

470
00:20:19,009 --> 00:20:20,528
or deliver noodles to her at midnight?

471
00:20:24,848 --> 00:20:25,409
Hao,

472
00:20:25,768 --> 00:20:26,568
I'm sorry.

473
00:20:27,128 --> 00:20:28,929
I didn't mean to tell him.

474
00:20:29,729 --> 00:20:30,608
What's wrong with you?

475
00:20:31,288 --> 00:20:33,889
Well, sorry about that.

476
00:20:33,889 --> 00:20:34,929
I take back what I said.

477
00:20:35,689 --> 00:20:36,169
It's fine.

478
00:20:36,169 --> 00:20:37,128
It's not fine.

479
00:20:39,848 --> 00:20:42,288
I recall your contract
expires next month.

480
00:20:43,169 --> 00:20:45,528
I'll tell HR not to renew your contract.

481
00:20:46,288 --> 00:20:46,929
Boss, I...

482
00:20:46,929 --> 00:20:49,048
Say one more word,

483
00:20:49,969 --> 00:20:51,288
and I'll fire you.

484
00:21:01,689 --> 00:21:02,689
I quit!

485
00:21:03,009 --> 00:21:03,568
Boss,

486
00:21:04,249 --> 00:21:06,009
Ding Wei's alright at his job.

487
00:21:06,128 --> 00:21:07,328
He just spouted some nonsense.

488
00:21:07,689 --> 00:21:08,360
Is it necessary?

489
00:21:08,808 --> 00:21:09,889
It is necessary.

490
00:21:11,449 --> 00:21:12,128
You're right.

491
00:21:12,768 --> 00:21:13,848
It was all nonsense.

492
00:21:14,249 --> 00:21:15,768
But there's too much nonsense.

493
00:21:16,209 --> 00:21:18,169
The best way to stop nonsense

494
00:21:18,368 --> 00:21:21,249
is to show them
there's a price for spreading rumors.

495
00:21:22,528 --> 00:21:23,768
I needed to send a message,

496
00:21:24,368 --> 00:21:25,729
and Ding Wei volunteered himself.

497
00:21:27,608 --> 00:21:28,009
Got it.

498
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:29,848
Go to work.

499
00:21:30,689 --> 00:21:31,128
Okay.

500
00:21:40,889 --> 00:21:41,689
So

501
00:21:42,048 --> 00:21:45,528
that analyst
Zhao Mei mentioned last time

502
00:21:46,689 --> 00:21:47,768
wasn't just random talk.

503
00:21:50,568 --> 00:21:51,768
I knew it.

504
00:21:52,169 --> 00:21:54,409
Dad, don't tell Mom about this.

505
00:21:54,409 --> 00:21:55,608
Or she'll lose sleep again.

506
00:21:57,969 --> 00:21:58,608
Got it.

507
00:21:58,929 --> 00:22:00,169
How much for the fish head?

508
00:22:00,328 --> 00:22:01,328
It's 18.8 yuan per jin.

509
00:22:01,969 --> 00:22:02,528
I'll take one.

510
00:22:04,088 --> 00:22:05,368
Clean it up properly for me.

511
00:22:05,368 --> 00:22:05,649
Okay.

512
00:22:06,729 --> 00:22:07,689
I'm getting a divorce.

513
00:22:07,689 --> 00:22:08,729
Is that your attitude?

514
00:22:09,808 --> 00:22:11,368
What attitude am I supposed to have?

515
00:22:12,009 --> 00:22:13,929
You're just here to inform me.

516
00:22:14,048 --> 00:22:16,209
Not to ask for my opinion.

517
00:22:17,009 --> 00:22:18,649
I'd have liked to ask for your opinion.

518
00:22:20,729 --> 00:22:22,128
I don't have any opinions.

519
00:22:22,368 --> 00:22:24,288
Everything that needed saying
has been said.

520
00:22:24,969 --> 00:22:27,409
I told you
not to let things blow up at home.

521
00:22:28,288 --> 00:22:29,808
I thought you understood.

522
00:22:29,929 --> 00:22:33,048
I didn't expect it to come to this.

523
00:22:34,649 --> 00:22:35,768
You're a smart person.

524
00:22:36,649 --> 00:22:39,409
Zhao Mei was clearly hinting
at you that day.

525
00:22:40,088 --> 00:22:41,689
How could you not pick up on that?

526
00:22:42,528 --> 00:22:44,608
You know what my relationship
with Zhao Mei is.

527
00:22:44,969 --> 00:22:46,568
It's always been me hitting at her.

528
00:22:46,729 --> 00:22:48,489
I never imagined
she'd hint at me someday.

529
00:22:48,489 --> 00:22:49,009
Alright.

530
00:22:49,249 --> 00:22:52,249
The problem with you
is you think too highly of yourself.

531
00:22:52,368 --> 00:22:53,249
And you blew it.

532
00:22:56,249 --> 00:22:57,328
What's Zhao Mei's stance?

533
00:22:58,009 --> 00:22:58,768
Does she insist?

534
00:22:59,128 --> 00:23:00,409
She seems quite determined.

535
00:23:04,808 --> 00:23:05,328
Okay.

536
00:23:06,128 --> 00:23:07,848
At least you two don't have children.

537
00:23:08,528 --> 00:23:09,449
Losses are manageable.

538
00:23:27,169 --> 00:23:28,128
I have a question.

539
00:23:29,489 --> 00:23:31,409
Have you thought about your next stop?

540
00:23:35,009 --> 00:23:36,169
More layoffs at the company?

541
00:23:37,328 --> 00:23:37,969
No.

542
00:23:38,169 --> 00:23:39,169
I was just asking.

543
00:23:43,649 --> 00:23:45,009
Even if layoffs aren't happening,

544
00:23:45,568 --> 00:23:47,128
you should still think about it.

545
00:23:48,048 --> 00:23:50,209
No one can stay at one company forever.

546
00:23:52,528 --> 00:23:54,024
Right now for me,

547
00:24:00,296 --> 00:24:01,489
I just want to follow you

548
00:24:03,328 --> 00:24:04,409
and learn more from you.

549
00:24:11,409 --> 00:24:12,409
What if I leave?

550
00:24:14,969 --> 00:24:16,209
Are you leaving Ruijin?

551
00:24:16,568 --> 00:24:17,848
I'm saying if.

552
00:24:18,689 --> 00:24:19,929
If a better opportunity arises,

553
00:24:20,489 --> 00:24:21,409
I'll definitely leave.

554
00:24:28,449 --> 00:24:29,409
I had a check-up lately.

555
00:24:30,528 --> 00:24:32,649
One tumor marker
came back very concerning.

556
00:24:33,608 --> 00:24:35,249
I was extremely anxious
during that time.

557
00:24:45,608 --> 00:24:48,889
I suspected
I had a malignant tumor before.

558
00:24:49,328 --> 00:24:51,568
But it was a false alarm
after reexamination.

559
00:24:51,729 --> 00:24:53,608
Our relationship feels like a tumor too,

560
00:24:53,608 --> 00:24:54,969
very harmful, even toxic.

561
00:24:55,729 --> 00:24:56,729
We should end it.

562
00:25:06,768 --> 00:25:07,288
Then...

563
00:25:07,288 --> 00:25:08,449
Let's correct course

564
00:25:09,009 --> 00:25:10,249
and get back to normal.

565
00:25:29,169 --> 00:25:29,689
Understood.

566
00:25:32,528 --> 00:25:33,088
I'm leaving.

567
00:25:56,409 --> 00:25:57,288
Check the second line.

568
00:26:03,592 --> 00:26:04,565
Hello.

569
00:26:05,409 --> 00:26:06,209
Is that Qiao Hailun?

570
00:26:06,848 --> 00:26:08,288
Please come to the HR office.

571
00:26:13,409 --> 00:26:14,528
I don't quite understand.

572
00:26:14,689 --> 00:26:16,128
Why reassign me to another project?

573
00:26:16,649 --> 00:26:18,969
Mr. Li didn't mention anything to me.

574
00:26:19,608 --> 00:26:20,808
Mr. Li is likely busy.

575
00:26:21,009 --> 00:26:22,048
He'll tell you later.

576
00:26:22,249 --> 00:26:23,729
Mr. Xiao's team is short-staffed.

577
00:26:24,009 --> 00:26:25,209
The project you're taking on

578
00:26:25,328 --> 00:26:26,768
is his biggest one for next year.

579
00:26:27,128 --> 00:26:28,088
Many wanted it.

580
00:26:28,368 --> 00:26:29,409
Seize the chance, alright?

581
00:26:31,449 --> 00:26:32,489
There's a desk right here.

582
00:26:32,969 --> 00:26:34,929
If you need any help, just let me know.

583
00:26:35,088 --> 00:26:36,209
Good luck. Do well.

584
00:27:01,969 --> 00:27:02,689
That woman?

585
00:27:03,169 --> 00:27:04,929
I don't buy
that there's nothing going on.

586
00:27:06,328 --> 00:27:08,689
(HR suddenly transferred me
to Mr. Xiao Yang's project.)

587
00:27:09,128 --> 00:27:10,209
(What's going on?)

588
00:27:12,128 --> 00:27:13,848
She claims she hasn't slept
with the boss?

589
00:27:13,848 --> 00:27:14,889
How is that possible?

590
00:27:15,169 --> 00:27:16,209
Is that true?

591
00:27:16,249 --> 00:27:18,048
She joined our company
right after graduation.

592
00:27:18,449 --> 00:27:19,528
Look how young she is.

593
00:27:19,528 --> 00:27:19,969
Yeah.

594
00:27:22,729 --> 00:27:23,409
Who knows?

595
00:27:39,929 --> 00:27:40,528
Mr. Li,

596
00:27:40,889 --> 00:27:41,889
HR just told me

597
00:27:42,209 --> 00:27:44,608
that I've been transferred
to Mr. Xiao's team.

598
00:27:45,568 --> 00:27:47,889
But I was doing fine
on my current project.

599
00:27:48,649 --> 00:27:49,768
Can I please stay?

600
00:27:49,889 --> 00:27:50,808
Why?

601
00:27:51,689 --> 00:27:52,209
Qiao Hailun,

602
00:27:52,889 --> 00:27:55,889
many fought tooth and nail
for a spot on this project.

603
00:27:57,169 --> 00:27:57,889
Hold on a second.

604
00:27:57,889 --> 00:27:59,449
I'll have Xiao Yang speak to you.

605
00:28:04,128 --> 00:28:05,449
Qiao Hailun,

606
00:28:05,889 --> 00:28:06,808
this is Xiao Yang.

607
00:28:07,368 --> 00:28:08,409
Mr. Xiao, hello.

608
00:28:09,169 --> 00:28:09,768
You know,

609
00:28:10,368 --> 00:28:12,929
the spot on the MT project
was already assigned to someone.

610
00:28:13,649 --> 00:28:16,048
I replaced that person for your sake.

611
00:28:16,048 --> 00:28:17,288
You must do an excellent job.

612
00:28:17,808 --> 00:28:19,808
Otherwise,
I can't explain it to the client.

613
00:28:24,489 --> 00:28:26,249
Qiao Hailun, listen.

614
00:28:26,768 --> 00:28:29,328
Many things in life
give you only one chance.

615
00:28:34,249 --> 00:28:34,889
I understand.

616
00:28:35,969 --> 00:28:36,568
Thanks, Mr. Li.

617
00:28:43,768 --> 00:28:46,969
How long are you planning
to have her on my team?

618
00:28:48,169 --> 00:28:49,249
I don't know.

619
00:28:50,128 --> 00:28:51,969
How about six months for a starter?

620
00:28:52,689 --> 00:28:53,649
If that doesn't work.

621
00:28:53,889 --> 00:28:56,969
I'll quietly arrange for her
to move to another company.

622
00:28:58,009 --> 00:28:58,929
To be honest,

623
00:28:59,169 --> 00:29:00,249
she's quite capable.

624
00:29:01,169 --> 00:29:02,088
In what way?

625
00:29:02,889 --> 00:29:04,169
Your wife is here.

626
00:29:05,528 --> 00:29:06,449
Take care.

627
00:29:06,449 --> 00:29:07,608
I need to go. See you.

628
00:29:08,169 --> 00:29:08,929
Thanks.

629
00:29:08,929 --> 00:29:09,768
No need for thanks.

630
00:29:09,768 --> 00:29:10,768
We're buddies.

631
00:29:11,409 --> 00:29:12,209
I've got your back.

632
00:29:15,528 --> 00:29:16,848
These are my initial selections.

633
00:29:17,128 --> 00:29:19,649
Take a look. If anyone catches your eye,
you can interview them.

634
00:29:20,608 --> 00:29:22,209
They're all from top universities.

635
00:29:22,528 --> 00:29:23,528
Graduate degree holders.

636
00:29:24,328 --> 00:29:25,729
Competition is fierce these days.

637
00:29:26,009 --> 00:29:27,128
It'll become the new normal.

638
00:29:28,889 --> 00:29:29,409
Thanks.

639
00:29:29,848 --> 00:29:31,209
I'll review and update you soon.

640
00:29:31,649 --> 00:29:32,169
Okay.

641
00:29:33,848 --> 00:29:34,689
Any plans tonight?

642
00:29:35,768 --> 00:29:36,969
It's the year-end promotion.

643
00:29:37,528 --> 00:29:38,368
You look stunning.

644
00:29:38,409 --> 00:29:39,169
Thank you.

645
00:29:39,169 --> 00:29:40,552
(Li Dongming.)

646
00:29:45,489 --> 00:29:46,288
I need to go.

647
00:29:46,288 --> 00:29:46,729
Okay.

648
00:29:49,768 --> 00:29:51,568
(Our relationship
feels like a tumor too,)

649
00:29:51,568 --> 00:29:53,169
(very harmful, even toxic.)

650
00:29:53,768 --> 00:29:54,689
(We should end it.)

651
00:30:02,368 --> 00:30:03,169
What's this?

652
00:30:04,048 --> 00:30:06,689
What's between me and Qiao Hailun
was my fault.

653
00:30:07,288 --> 00:30:08,768
I've transferred her out of my team.

654
00:30:09,288 --> 00:30:11,689
I'll find a way
to have her leave the company later.

655
00:30:12,368 --> 00:30:13,929
I will correct every mistake I made.

656
00:30:14,889 --> 00:30:19,368
I hope you'll cherish the happy memories
from our two years.

657
00:30:20,368 --> 00:30:22,929
I hope you'll give me another chance.

658
00:30:23,048 --> 00:30:24,449
No need to reply right now.

659
00:30:25,649 --> 00:30:26,449
Think it over.

660
00:30:28,568 --> 00:30:29,169
You go ahead.

661
00:30:46,009 --> 00:30:46,689
It's 25-year.

662
00:30:48,088 --> 00:30:49,768
Only you could do this, Mr. Dong.

663
00:30:49,889 --> 00:30:50,409
Impressive.

664
00:30:50,889 --> 00:30:51,209
Amazing.

665
00:30:51,209 --> 00:30:52,249
Pretty standard flavor.

666
00:30:53,969 --> 00:30:55,409
You're treating tomorrow.

667
00:30:55,409 --> 00:30:56,009
Don't forget.

668
00:31:13,328 --> 00:31:14,009
Are you okay?

669
00:31:16,368 --> 00:31:17,368
Your husband just left.

670
00:31:20,328 --> 00:31:20,969
I'm fine.

671
00:31:25,929 --> 00:31:26,409
Alright.

672
00:31:32,048 --> 00:31:33,169
All three bottles sold?

673
00:31:33,568 --> 00:31:34,249
That's great.

674
00:31:35,328 --> 00:31:36,649
Don't pay me in cash.

675
00:31:36,649 --> 00:31:37,608
It's inconvenient.

676
00:31:37,608 --> 00:31:38,768
Just transfer it to me.

677
00:31:39,169 --> 00:31:39,889
How many more?

678
00:31:40,649 --> 00:31:41,288
Three?

679
00:31:41,288 --> 00:31:42,689
Okay, no problem.

680
00:31:42,689 --> 00:31:43,689
I'll bring them tomorrow.

681
00:31:46,608 --> 00:31:49,169
Fine. I'll pull an all-nighter.

682
00:31:49,169 --> 00:31:51,249
I'll deliver them overnight. Satisfied?

683
00:31:51,689 --> 00:31:52,409
Okay, bye.

684
00:31:53,249 --> 00:31:54,409
Ms. Liang, making a fortune?

685
00:31:55,368 --> 00:31:57,128
Not at all.

686
00:31:57,209 --> 00:31:59,768
It's all thanks to you people
supporting me.

687
00:32:00,368 --> 00:32:01,088
Enjoy your meal.

688
00:32:01,449 --> 00:32:01,929
Thanks.

689
00:32:05,409 --> 00:32:06,209
Sixteen places.

690
00:32:06,209 --> 00:32:07,288
Fifty-two bottles daily.

691
00:32:07,288 --> 00:32:11,328
That's 1560 bottles monthly.

692
00:32:17,169 --> 00:32:17,729
Mr. Lv.

693
00:32:20,128 --> 00:32:20,768
No problem.

694
00:32:20,768 --> 00:32:22,249
Just have your friend contact me.

695
00:32:24,128 --> 00:32:25,048
Okay. No worries.

696
00:32:25,169 --> 00:32:26,009
I'll deliver them.

697
00:32:27,929 --> 00:32:31,169
Your friend gets the same deal as you.

698
00:32:33,328 --> 00:32:35,128
No problem. Okay.

699
00:32:39,249 --> 00:32:39,969
Mr. Lv.

700
00:32:42,288 --> 00:32:43,729
Boss, you wanted to see me?

701
00:32:43,729 --> 00:32:44,488
Close the door.

702
00:32:49,929 --> 00:32:50,568
What's wrong?

703
00:32:50,808 --> 00:32:53,512
I heard about you fronting the cost
for those small restaurants.

704
00:32:56,009 --> 00:32:56,936
Who told you to do it?

705
00:32:58,249 --> 00:33:00,969
You're basically being the company's
main distributor, you know?

706
00:33:01,489 --> 00:33:03,929
I thought the amounts were small, so...

707
00:33:03,929 --> 00:33:05,009
What do you mean 'small'?

708
00:33:05,249 --> 00:33:06,848
Any amount is a serious violation.

709
00:33:08,009 --> 00:33:10,088
You can't be both the seller
and the distributor.

710
00:33:10,608 --> 00:33:11,808
Make it clear to your clients.

711
00:33:11,808 --> 00:33:13,808
We only accept payment before delivery.

712
00:33:13,808 --> 00:33:14,729
If you refuse,

713
00:33:15,729 --> 00:33:16,936
explain it to Internal Audit.

714
00:33:17,568 --> 00:33:18,489
Okay, got it.

715
00:33:18,489 --> 00:33:19,209
I'll handle it.

716
00:33:20,808 --> 00:33:21,409
Thanks, boss.

717
00:33:23,209 --> 00:33:23,848
Make it quick.

718
00:33:24,088 --> 00:33:24,568
Okay.

719
00:33:27,889 --> 00:33:31,169
That's the total sales volume
for my territory in Q3.

720
00:33:31,489 --> 00:33:32,288
Initial estimates:

721
00:33:32,288 --> 00:33:35,368
Q4 sales will increase
by 50 percent over Q3.

722
00:33:35,889 --> 00:33:38,128
That 50 percent is driven
by channel stuffing, right?

723
00:33:39,489 --> 00:33:40,009
Dong Yue,

724
00:33:40,009 --> 00:33:42,449
do you know Shen Mo's current inventory?

725
00:33:43,328 --> 00:33:44,009
I know,

726
00:33:44,288 --> 00:33:45,848
but the numbers came from him.

727
00:33:45,848 --> 00:33:46,528
Hard to verify.

728
00:33:48,088 --> 00:33:49,649
That's the core issue.

729
00:33:51,889 --> 00:33:53,368
Goods appear sold,

730
00:33:53,528 --> 00:33:55,768
but they're in fact piled up
in distributors' warehouses.

731
00:33:56,048 --> 00:33:58,568
Until they reach end consumers,

732
00:33:58,969 --> 00:34:00,209
those sales figures are fake.

733
00:34:00,608 --> 00:34:02,808
We don't know actual sales volume

734
00:34:02,808 --> 00:34:04,889
or how long the surplus
will take to sell.

735
00:34:05,128 --> 00:34:07,568
And production planning
becomes impossible.

736
00:34:08,009 --> 00:34:08,769
It's all fake.

737
00:34:08,929 --> 00:34:12,289
We considered subtracting store
from company shipments

738
00:34:12,289 --> 00:34:14,048
to calculate Shen Mo's stock.

739
00:34:14,048 --> 00:34:15,208
But we're short-staffed.

740
00:34:15,688 --> 00:34:19,208
Xinhe District alone
has over 200 stores.

741
00:34:19,208 --> 00:34:21,528
Our sales team can't cover them all.

742
00:34:25,449 --> 00:34:27,528
Zhao Mei, you have more people.

743
00:34:28,009 --> 00:34:29,728
You have over 500 promoters.

744
00:34:29,809 --> 00:34:32,889
You can have them
quietly check actual store sales.

745
00:34:34,929 --> 00:34:36,369
We could,

746
00:34:37,289 --> 00:34:40,208
but I worry if Shen Mo finds out,

747
00:34:40,648 --> 00:34:41,769
he'll be very upset.

748
00:34:42,128 --> 00:34:44,168
Shen Mo's a Tier-1 distributor.

749
00:34:44,809 --> 00:34:46,889
If we start with smaller stores,

750
00:34:47,048 --> 00:34:48,289
he likely won't notice.

751
00:34:49,849 --> 00:34:50,809
Dong Yue, any thoughts?

752
00:34:50,809 --> 00:34:51,889
You know him better.

753
00:34:52,248 --> 00:34:53,088
It should be doable.

754
00:35:01,369 --> 00:35:02,128
Let me think.

755
00:35:05,728 --> 00:35:06,329
Boss,

756
00:35:06,969 --> 00:35:11,248
using promoters
to audit store sales is risky.

757
00:35:12,128 --> 00:35:13,409
If distributors find out,

758
00:35:13,409 --> 00:35:14,289
it'll blow up.

759
00:35:15,728 --> 00:35:17,369
The risk is huge,

760
00:35:24,329 --> 00:35:26,009
but so is the opportunity.

761
00:35:29,769 --> 00:35:31,568
Sales territory is limited.

762
00:35:31,568 --> 00:35:33,889
And we're muscling in.

763
00:35:35,769 --> 00:35:36,969
To stand out,

764
00:35:36,969 --> 00:35:38,969
we need unique strengths.

765
00:35:39,168 --> 00:35:42,329
Ours is the promo team.

766
00:35:42,329 --> 00:35:43,769
We outnumber them

767
00:35:43,769 --> 00:35:45,409
and cover all retail points.

768
00:35:46,208 --> 00:35:49,208
If we get the real sales data,

769
00:35:52,489 --> 00:35:53,568
not just Dong Yue,

770
00:35:54,449 --> 00:35:58,409
even Barry and Peter
will come begging to me.

771
00:36:00,232 --> 00:36:03,029
(Happy Birthday)

772
00:36:08,688 --> 00:36:09,168
Come in.

773
00:36:11,128 --> 00:36:13,409
Ms. Qi, it's your birthday?

774
00:36:14,489 --> 00:36:15,568
A big occasion.

775
00:36:16,648 --> 00:36:17,289
I...

776
00:36:17,289 --> 00:36:19,208
Stop. Business first.

777
00:36:19,449 --> 00:36:19,889
Okay.

778
00:36:21,449 --> 00:36:22,009
Well?

779
00:36:22,809 --> 00:36:23,329
Found it.

780
00:36:24,849 --> 00:36:28,409
The one who took the photo uploaded it
anonymously from a personal phone.

781
00:36:29,248 --> 00:36:30,168
But she was careless

782
00:36:30,688 --> 00:36:31,889
and used the company network.

783
00:36:34,449 --> 00:36:35,048
Who was it?

784
00:36:37,248 --> 00:36:38,208
You'll never guess.

785
00:36:46,849 --> 00:36:47,409
Zixuan,

786
00:36:47,849 --> 00:36:49,048
I've been meaning to ask you.

787
00:36:49,648 --> 00:36:51,728
How's working in that big office?

788
00:36:54,208 --> 00:36:55,329
Honestly?

789
00:36:56,969 --> 00:36:57,728
Awesome.

790
00:36:58,769 --> 00:37:02,688
Office work is way simpler
than promotions.

791
00:37:02,769 --> 00:37:03,449
Seriously?

792
00:37:05,009 --> 00:37:05,809
Totally.

793
00:37:06,329 --> 00:37:07,728
They just sit through meetings.

794
00:37:08,128 --> 00:37:10,289
There are meetings for everything.

795
00:37:10,528 --> 00:37:12,608
(Fang, GST Liquor)
And they do whatever the boss says.

796
00:37:12,608 --> 00:37:14,608
(Veteran Promoter, 7 yrs exp)
No need for their own ideas.

797
00:37:14,969 --> 00:37:16,449
If data comes from other depts,

798
00:37:16,449 --> 00:37:18,128
they just compile it.

799
00:37:18,929 --> 00:37:19,528
The other day,

800
00:37:19,688 --> 00:37:21,208
at the Nansha dinner,

801
00:37:21,369 --> 00:37:23,168
I also didn't do anything hard.

802
00:37:23,168 --> 00:37:24,088
Just helped out.

803
00:37:24,849 --> 00:37:26,728
It's nothing like frontline promotions,

804
00:37:26,969 --> 00:37:28,809
where we have to answer questions,

805
00:37:28,809 --> 00:37:30,728
build store relations,

806
00:37:30,728 --> 00:37:31,889
track data,

807
00:37:31,889 --> 00:37:33,128
handle complaints,

808
00:37:33,688 --> 00:37:35,728
and dodge surprise checks.

809
00:37:35,969 --> 00:37:37,648
We're way tougher.

810
00:37:41,489 --> 00:37:43,248
They sit.

811
00:37:43,688 --> 00:37:44,688
We can only stand.

812
00:37:44,688 --> 00:37:45,088
Right.

813
00:37:46,489 --> 00:37:48,728
And their salary
isn't much higher than ours, right?

814
00:37:49,128 --> 00:37:50,728
I mean for the most junior ones.

815
00:37:50,728 --> 00:37:51,329
Pretty much.

816
00:37:52,208 --> 00:37:54,009
When we work as promoters,

817
00:37:54,688 --> 00:37:55,769
we even fight.

818
00:37:56,449 --> 00:37:57,688
Do they need to fight?

819
00:37:58,289 --> 00:38:01,329
Tell me, who wants to fight these days?

820
00:38:03,009 --> 00:38:04,168
But then again.

821
00:38:04,769 --> 00:38:07,009
If it's so bad,

822
00:38:07,009 --> 00:38:09,648
why does everyone want to work
in an office building?

823
00:38:11,688 --> 00:38:12,648
Let me tell you.

824
00:38:13,648 --> 00:38:15,088
Because there's a future.

825
00:38:15,449 --> 00:38:19,608
One might be a lowly specialist today.

826
00:38:20,048 --> 00:38:22,688
But in the future,
they might become a director or manager.

827
00:38:23,128 --> 00:38:24,728
And they might even become a boss.

828
00:38:24,728 --> 00:38:25,489
What about us?

829
00:38:26,128 --> 00:38:28,009
Junior promoters.

830
00:38:28,849 --> 00:38:30,929
Senior promoters.

831
00:38:32,289 --> 00:38:34,208
And veteran promoters.

832
00:38:34,648 --> 00:38:35,168
Really.

833
00:38:35,168 --> 00:38:37,128
Maybe we'll work until we're 80

834
00:38:40,128 --> 00:38:42,009
and still be promoters.

835
00:38:56,769 --> 00:38:57,409
Sorry.

836
00:38:57,849 --> 00:38:59,048
On such a happy day,

837
00:38:59,048 --> 00:39:00,769
I shouldn't have said those things.

838
00:39:00,769 --> 00:39:01,728
No offense intended.

839
00:39:01,969 --> 00:39:02,568
You work hard.

840
00:39:02,568 --> 00:39:03,128
It's okay.

841
00:39:04,289 --> 00:39:05,449
Once you've made it,

842
00:39:05,728 --> 00:39:08,329
you might become a big boss.

843
00:39:08,528 --> 00:39:10,009
Then we'll tell people

844
00:39:11,528 --> 00:39:13,969
that you're our friend.

845
